WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.368 --> 00:00:03.460
Baba Voss!

2
00:00:03.545 --> 00:00:05.463
Would you really let your children die

3
00:00:05.547 --> 00:00:08.179
protecting the family
that sold your daughter to Edo?

4
00:00:12.304 --> 00:00:14.055
- The bombs?
- Ready to move.

5
00:00:14.139 --> 00:00:17.100
We are going to destroy Pennsa
and everyone in it.

6
00:00:18.769 --> 00:00:20.145
Oh. shit. I'm so sorry.

7
00:00:20.229 --> 00:00:21.313
Drop the gun.

8
00:00:22.189 --> 00:00:24.065
Stop! Stop!

9
00:00:24.149 --> 00:00:25.525
- Stop it! Both of you!
- What did you do?

10
00:00:25.609 --> 00:00:26.651
We have to get out of here!

11
00:00:26.735 --> 00:00:29.796
Haniwa.

12
00:00:31.428 --> 00:00:33.907
- <i>Tormada's not here.</i>
<i>- And he took the bombs.</i>

13
00:00:34.007 --> 00:00:38.037
Which is why we need to get to Pennsa.
Raise the alarm. Meet them with an army.

14
00:00:38.121 --> 00:00:39.956
<i>The Witchfinders
have grown too bold.</i>

15
00:00:40.204 --> 00:00:44.041
Violation of your queen's edict
is punishable by death.

16
00:00:44.362 --> 00:00:47.390
I am going to take back
the throne of my father.

17
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:50.759
And I ask you now to fight by my side!

18
00:00:50.843 --> 00:00:57.311
The true defenders of Paya!

19
00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:05.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

20
00:01:08.364 --> 00:01:10.073
I want men posted at their church

21
00:01:10.157 --> 00:01:12.097
and each of their homes
in case they return.

22
00:01:12.182 --> 00:01:13.830
I don't believe
the Witchfinders will be

23
00:01:13.915 --> 00:01:15.704
returning home
anytime soon.

24
00:01:15.788 --> 00:01:17.415
You've outlawed their beliefs.

25
00:01:17.500 --> 00:01:19.790
Well. their beliefs have been outlawed
in all of Paya.

26
00:01:19.875 --> 00:01:21.314
Where will they go?

27
00:01:21.652 --> 00:01:23.552
Ah. It's a big kingdom.

28
00:01:24.551 --> 00:01:29.325
My guess is the outer-lying towns.
uh. Lebnin. Al to on a.

29
00:01:29.419 --> 00:01:31.778
they'll find a more sympathetic haven.

30
00:01:32.191 --> 00:01:35.088
Have Lords Diego and Torrance sent word?
I want them found.

31
00:01:35.182 --> 00:01:36.588
Already did.

32
00:01:36.851 --> 00:01:40.254
Perhaps we'll have news.
The council is already assembled.

33
00:01:40.338 --> 00:01:42.276
Any word on my family?

34
00:01:42.439 --> 00:01:45.442
Even if everything at
the House of Enlightenment went perfectly.

35
00:01:45.526 --> 00:01:47.093
they wouldn't be back yet.

36
00:01:47.945 --> 00:01:49.955
When does anything go perfectly?

37
00:01:56.524 --> 00:01:58.883
You said the council
had already assembled?

38
00:01:59.206 --> 00:02:00.439
It has.

39
00:02:02.050 --> 00:02:03.575
Why don't I hear them?

40
00:02:11.449 --> 00:02:12.939
I smell blood.

41
00:02:40.436 --> 00:02:41.669
Is it all of them?

42
00:02:42.926 --> 00:02:44.400
I think so.

43
00:02:55.917 --> 00:02:57.651
Lord Diego.

44
00:03:06.609 --> 00:03:08.051
Witchfinders.

45
00:03:08.369 --> 00:03:11.830
Blood is still warm.
Let's get you somewhere safe.

46
00:04:35.678 --> 00:04:37.870
<font color=#FF00FF>*SEE *</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 03 Episode 06</font>

47
00:04:37.954 --> 00:04:40.588
Episode Title: <font color=#FFc30f>"The Lowlands"</font>
Aired on: <font color=#00ffff>September 30. 2022.</font>

48
00:04:51.032 --> 00:04:54.394
- Okay. this isn't gonna work.
- What are you talking about?

49
00:04:55.589 --> 00:04:57.722
We don't just need
to get to Pennsa before Tormada.

50
00:04:57.806 --> 00:05:00.117
We gotta get there
with enough time to build an army.

51
00:05:00.201 --> 00:05:02.661
fortify defenses. come up with a plan.

52
00:05:02.745 --> 00:05:04.167
You know a faster way?

53
00:05:04.251 --> 00:05:06.485
Well. yes. actually I do.

54
00:05:08.293 --> 00:05:11.353
There's another route
sometimes used by smugglers.

55
00:05:11.713 --> 00:05:13.947
Why are you only saying this now?

56
00:05:14.966 --> 00:05:16.853
'Cause it's dangerous. okay?

57
00:05:17.681 --> 00:05:20.551
But it'll save us an entire day.
Maybe two.

58
00:05:20.635 --> 00:05:25.208
You wanna take 'em through the lowlands?
Yeah. you're crazy.

59
00:05:25.477 --> 00:05:26.769
What are these lowlands?

60
00:05:26.853 --> 00:05:32.733
They aren't on any maps.
And the terrain is-is... is tricky.

61
00:05:32.817 --> 00:05:35.385
- What do you mean "tricky"?
- We've lost men there.

62
00:05:35.653 --> 00:05:37.154
- Lost them? How?
- We don't know.

63
00:05:37.238 --> 00:05:39.264
- There are spirits.
- Not that.

64
00:05:39.532 --> 00:05:42.910
Okay. it's not ideal.
but it's the fastest way back.

65
00:05:42.994 --> 00:05:45.348
And there are seven of us.
Three of us have sight.

66
00:05:45.644 --> 00:05:48.337
I've made it through many times
with far less.

67
00:05:49.417 --> 00:05:50.817
How many times?

68
00:05:55.840 --> 00:05:57.073
Twice.

69
00:05:59.636 --> 00:06:01.327
You'll lead the way.

70
00:06:01.679 --> 00:06:06.249
Yeah. right. Punish the one with the plan.

71
00:06:22.325 --> 00:06:24.994
How did we let these Witchfinders
get past our defenses?

72
00:06:25.078 --> 00:06:29.022
It wasn't a lot of them.
Three or four is all it would've taken.

73
00:06:29.374 --> 00:06:31.691
Those were largely defenseless civilians.

74
00:06:32.043 --> 00:06:33.526
I did this.

75
00:06:33.683 --> 00:06:34.692
Maghra.

76
00:06:34.776 --> 00:06:37.215
I had them in my hands.
moments from the hangman.

77
00:06:37.299 --> 00:06:39.300
And I just let them go.

78
00:06:39.384 --> 00:06:40.639
You showed mercy.

79
00:06:40.723 --> 00:06:43.790
My mercy just killed our entire council.

80
00:06:51.166 --> 00:06:52.732
My sister was right.

81
00:06:55.483 --> 00:06:59.594
Violence must be met with violence.

82
00:07:02.157 --> 00:07:04.808
I'm gonna find these Witchfinders.

83
00:07:05.451 --> 00:07:08.634
They are murderers. and they will pay.

84
00:07:09.539 --> 00:07:14.335
I only ask you leave this with me.
Your hands should stay clean.

85
00:07:14.419 --> 00:07:16.069
It's too late for that.

86
00:07:56.669 --> 00:07:59.279
Whoa. whoa! Whoa.

87
00:08:00.840 --> 00:08:05.700
Welcome. Councillor.
Made exceptional time.

88
00:08:06.846 --> 00:08:11.114
I received word you managed to lose
an entire battalion to one man.

89
00:08:11.351 --> 00:08:13.084
A man you said you killed.

90
00:08:13.728 --> 00:08:17.189
Yes. yes. yes. Baba Voss.

91
00:08:17.273 --> 00:08:19.358
All my fault. lesson learned and so on.

92
00:08:19.442 --> 00:08:22.568
But. uh. why talk about past mistakes

93
00:08:22.653 --> 00:08:24.348
when we can talk about
how many soldiers you brought me?

94
00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:28.247
Pathetically few.
I had to be careful.

95
00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:30.703
Until I've bought
the loyalties of the generals.

96
00:08:30.787 --> 00:08:32.621
I cannot reveal my part in all of this.

97
00:08:32.705 --> 00:08:34.623
Hmm. reasonable calculation.

98
00:08:34.707 --> 00:08:38.359
Maybe. But we're a regiment short.

99
00:08:38.795 --> 00:08:40.504
Can we still take Pennsa?

100
00:08:40.588 --> 00:08:45.575
Ah. you still underestimate
the power of my bombs.

101
00:08:47.345 --> 00:08:50.473
I'm concerned about
having enough soldiers to place them.

102
00:08:50.557 --> 00:08:52.582
Ah. soldiers are no longer required.

103
00:08:52.851 --> 00:08:56.836
We've built machines that can
launch these bombs great distances.

104
00:08:57.772 --> 00:09:01.674
- You've tested these machines?
- You insult me.

105
00:09:03.528 --> 00:09:05.279
And the sighted children?

106
00:09:05.363 --> 00:09:07.406
How will you continue to operate
without them?

107
00:09:07.490 --> 00:09:10.534
We'll find them.
And there are other sighted ones in play.

108
00:09:10.618 --> 00:09:13.204
In the meantime.
we have more than enough ammunition

109
00:09:13.288 --> 00:09:16.272
to flatten the entire Payan kingdom.

110
00:09:17.584 --> 00:09:21.861
Well. then.
I suppose you should proceed to Pennsa.

111
00:09:22.213 --> 00:09:24.030
You have my troops.

112
00:09:24.299 --> 00:09:26.717
- For which. you have my thanks.
- Commander.

113
00:09:26.801 --> 00:09:28.844
Join ranks!

114
00:09:28.928 --> 00:09:30.262
Back home?

115
00:09:30.346 --> 00:09:34.290
Yes. I have an empire in crisis to manage.

116
00:09:34.558 --> 00:09:37.251
And you have a kingdom to conquer.

117
00:09:40.668 --> 00:09:42.068
Safe travels.

118
00:09:42.586 --> 00:09:43.819
Hyah!

119
00:10:14.552 --> 00:10:20.973
Harlan. in a lifetime of bad ideas.
this is the worst.

120
00:10:21.232 --> 00:10:24.652
Yeah.
There's no turning back now.

121
00:10:27.237 --> 00:10:29.471
You should talk to your sister.

122
00:10:29.707 --> 00:10:31.434
She shot a gun at me.

123
00:10:32.903 --> 00:10:38.590
Kofun. do you know why your mother will be
a far better queen than Sibeth?

124
00:10:39.723 --> 00:10:42.262
No. 'Cause she's not crazy?

125
00:10:43.961 --> 00:10:45.894
'Cause she has compassion.

126
00:10:46.381 --> 00:10:47.673
I could never be king

127
00:10:47.757 --> 00:10:51.826
'cause my compassion is less powerful
than my instinct to fight.

128
00:10:52.637 --> 00:10:55.264
Maybe that's what makes a good warrior.
I don't know.

129
00:10:55.348 --> 00:10:58.666
But what I do know is
that you are your mother's son.

130
00:10:59.269 --> 00:11:02.921
You have had her compassion
and wisdom from a young age.

131
00:11:03.773 --> 00:11:07.592
I know you think that makes you soft.
but it makes you stronger.

132
00:11:09.112 --> 00:11:12.222
Like your mother.
You'll make a great king.

133
00:11:15.201 --> 00:11:16.410
What?

134
00:11:16.494 --> 00:11:19.062
What are you talking about?
I'm not gonna be king.

135
00:11:19.497 --> 00:11:21.106
Spoken like a true prince.

136
00:11:22.333 --> 00:11:24.984
Please. go talk to your sister.

137
00:11:27.422 --> 00:11:28.964
It's not gonna work.

138
00:11:29.048 --> 00:11:30.532
That's the spirit. boy.

139
00:11:35.263 --> 00:11:36.496
Hey.

140
00:11:38.224 --> 00:11:40.458
- I'll leave the two of you alone.
- Wren.

141
00:11:41.394 --> 00:11:44.337
- We have to talk at some point.
- Do we?

142
00:11:45.857 --> 00:11:49.551
It wasn't just me. you know.
Mom and Dad wanted it gone too.

143
00:11:50.945 --> 00:11:53.948
The knowledge stored in that place
could've changed the world.

144
00:11:54.032 --> 00:11:57.576
You think I don't know that?
Haniwa. they were building bombs.

145
00:11:57.660 --> 00:12:00.895
They are building bombs. Not us.

146
00:12:02.081 --> 00:12:03.481
We would be different.

147
00:12:04.792 --> 00:12:06.627
You were pretty quick to pick up that gun.

148
00:12:09.047 --> 00:12:11.465
I'm sorry. That was a mistake.

149
00:12:11.549 --> 00:12:13.134
Yeah. it was a pretty big mistake.

150
00:12:13.218 --> 00:12:16.745
Please. as if you haven't
made mistakes. Sibeth.

151
00:12:21.518 --> 00:12:24.085
Papa. what is it?

152
00:12:24.896 --> 00:12:26.296
We're not alone.

153
00:12:26.689 --> 00:12:28.590
This fucking place.

154
00:12:41.287 --> 00:12:42.604
I saw someone.

155
00:12:44.082 --> 00:12:45.982
There's another.

156
00:12:47.919 --> 00:12:49.003
There are more.

157
00:12:50.839 --> 00:12:52.280
At least six.

158
00:12:56.636 --> 00:12:59.305
We can handle six. Right?

159
00:13:02.225 --> 00:13:03.458
Hello!

160
00:13:04.018 --> 00:13:06.211
We're passing through.
We mean you no harm.

161
00:13:08.189 --> 00:13:11.674
But… we are heavily armed.

162
00:13:16.239 --> 00:13:17.555
They have dogs.

163
00:13:19.325 --> 00:13:20.659
Those aren't dogs.

164
00:13:23.913 --> 00:13:26.314
Whoa! Shit.

165
00:13:35.800 --> 00:13:37.032
Guntar!

166
00:14:23.556 --> 00:14:26.958
Oh! Fuck! Shit! No!

167
00:14:33.024 --> 00:14:35.258
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

168
00:14:36.820 --> 00:14:38.053
Oh. fuck.

169
00:15:06.850 --> 00:15:09.626
- Kofun. Are you hurt?
- No.

170
00:15:10.937 --> 00:15:12.337
Where's Haniwa?

171
00:15:15.942 --> 00:15:20.654
Get the fuck off!

172
00:15:20.738 --> 00:15:22.573
Haniwa!

173
00:15:48.808 --> 00:15:50.125
Haniwa.

174
00:16:00.069 --> 00:16:01.445
Baba!

175
00:16:01.529 --> 00:16:03.697
- Where is she?
- They took her.

176
00:16:03.781 --> 00:16:04.782
She's gone.

177
00:16:36.314 --> 00:16:37.756
Whoa.

178
00:16:38.733 --> 00:16:41.134
Whoa.

179
00:16:44.322 --> 00:16:47.057
What is it? Why are we stopping?

180
00:16:47.784 --> 00:16:50.060
There's someone on the road. sir.

181
00:16:51.746 --> 00:16:54.039
What is that?

182
00:17:02.841 --> 00:17:04.491
Stand down.

183
00:17:05.927 --> 00:17:07.369
Stand down!

184
00:17:10.849 --> 00:17:13.208
Who are you? What do you want?

185
00:17:14.477 --> 00:17:16.294
I'm seeking Tormada.

186
00:17:17.856 --> 00:17:19.339
I am Tormada.

187
00:17:22.068 --> 00:17:23.510
I'll do it.

188
00:17:24.028 --> 00:17:25.428
Get off me.

189
00:17:36.541 --> 00:17:37.816
And who might you be?

190
00:17:39.335 --> 00:17:41.778
Tormada. I am Sibeth Kane.

191
00:17:52.474 --> 00:17:57.127
Your Majesty. It is an honor.

192
00:18:04.402 --> 00:18:08.012
Hmm. I'd heard you were a smart one.

193
00:18:08.655 --> 00:18:13.560
Now. where are all those wonderful weapons
I've heard so much about?

194
00:18:18.124 --> 00:18:19.607
Is that human bone?

195
00:18:20.376 --> 00:18:22.694
What are these?

196
00:18:23.213 --> 00:18:25.405
I heard stories about this
when I was a boy.

197
00:18:25.757 --> 00:18:29.826
There's a tribe that lives like animals.
Hunting and eating their own kind.

198
00:18:30.220 --> 00:18:33.830
I heard those stories too.
Fucking flesh eaters.

199
00:18:34.349 --> 00:18:37.167
Cannibals. We read about them.

200
00:18:38.019 --> 00:18:40.646
All right. well. what are we gonna do?
We have to find them.

201
00:18:40.730 --> 00:18:42.773
We should split up.
Search the entire area.

202
00:18:42.857 --> 00:18:45.717
No. that's gonna take too long.
We'll be too late.

203
00:18:46.069 --> 00:18:49.054
Maybe not.
They took them alive for a reason.

204
00:18:49.405 --> 00:18:51.037
What are you trying to say?

205
00:18:53.201 --> 00:18:56.352
They keep them alive
so that they don't spoil.

206
00:18:58.832 --> 00:19:02.918
Kofun. I need you to ride back to Pennsa.
tell your mother Tormada's coming.

207
00:19:03.002 --> 00:19:05.779
No. No. I'm not leaving. Haniwa needs me.

208
00:19:06.756 --> 00:19:08.424
So does your son and your mother.

209
00:19:08.508 --> 00:19:10.676
Get on the horse
and ride to Pennsa and warn her now.

210
00:19:10.760 --> 00:19:11.993
Wren. with me.

211
00:19:12.637 --> 00:19:15.163
We're gonna get her back.

212
00:19:41.583 --> 00:19:44.317
- Remend Skelt.
- Who's that?

213
00:19:46.546 --> 00:19:48.029
Tamacti Jun.

214
00:19:49.924 --> 00:19:51.366
Tamacti Jun.

215
00:19:51.885 --> 00:19:54.452
I'd heard of your return from the dead.

216
00:19:56.097 --> 00:20:00.750
and no sooner are you back
than you disband the army that you served.

217
00:20:01.019 --> 00:20:03.086
I serve the queen.

218
00:20:03.897 --> 00:20:07.340
And you have aligned yourself

219
00:20:07.859 --> 00:20:13.179
with those who would undermine her crown.

220
00:20:15.408 --> 00:20:19.144
I'm a simple blacksmith.
I'm not aligned with anyone.

221
00:20:21.080 --> 00:20:22.313
Well. then…

222
00:20:23.958 --> 00:20:25.775
It's time you were.

223
00:20:26.085 --> 00:20:27.485
My queen.

224
00:20:32.133 --> 00:20:35.469
Hello. Remend. is it?

225
00:20:35.553 --> 00:20:37.037
Your Majesty.

226
00:20:37.889 --> 00:20:39.873
I'm looking for some Witchfinders.

227
00:20:40.266 --> 00:20:43.585
The Witchfinders have all
been disbanded. my queen.

228
00:20:44.062 --> 00:20:47.338
Hmm. Are you sure
that's how you want this to go?

229
00:20:48.983 --> 00:20:50.359
Tamacti Jun.

230
00:21:04.290 --> 00:21:07.668
- Where are they?
- I don't know! I don't!

231
00:21:13.466 --> 00:21:15.992
Put his hand on the table.

232
00:21:16.594 --> 00:21:22.082
This is a whistle sword.

233
00:21:22.892 --> 00:21:24.709
I doubt you've ever made one.

234
00:21:25.176 --> 00:21:28.527
It requires a level of artistry
that few possess.

235
00:21:29.440 --> 00:21:33.259
Its blade is refined
to an almost inhuman level of precision.

236
00:21:33.611 --> 00:21:38.890
These Witchfinders we're looking for
just slaughtered 12 innocent Payans.

237
00:21:39.993 --> 00:21:43.019
If they are not found.
they will keep killing.

238
00:21:44.455 --> 00:21:48.066
So. please.
will you tell us where they are?

239
00:21:49.627 --> 00:21:51.212
I will not.

240
00:21:53.131 --> 00:21:54.563
I understand.

241
00:21:58.970 --> 00:22:01.305
You can probably keep making
your swords without that finger.

242
00:22:01.389 --> 00:22:03.432
but what happens when I take your thumb?

243
00:22:03.516 --> 00:22:05.559
No. fuck!

244
00:22:05.643 --> 00:22:07.686
No! They're at the mason's yard.

245
00:22:07.770 --> 00:22:09.605
There's a house in the back.
They're all in there.

246
00:22:13.401 --> 00:22:14.634
Thank you.

247
00:22:19.324 --> 00:22:23.619
You fucking heretic!
I hope they slit your fucking throat.

248
00:22:23.703 --> 00:22:26.247
You and those bastard witch children!

249
00:22:26.331 --> 00:22:28.064
Take the whole hand.

250
00:22:47.977 --> 00:22:49.377
Yes. This way.

251
00:22:52.440 --> 00:22:54.215
Edo used to track like this.

252
00:22:57.153 --> 00:23:00.055
My father. he was a Slaver.

253
00:23:01.282 --> 00:23:03.099
He taught us to track this way.

254
00:23:06.871 --> 00:23:09.606
Scared men. they leave marks.

255
00:23:10.458 --> 00:23:11.983
They make mistakes.

256
00:23:14.587 --> 00:23:19.407
But these. these things…

257
00:23:24.055 --> 00:23:25.890
Have no fear.

258
00:23:25.974 --> 00:23:28.416
You lost it?

259
00:23:29.727 --> 00:23:30.959
Anything?

260
00:23:32.647 --> 00:23:34.214
They leave no trail.

261
00:23:41.239 --> 00:23:42.239
They are hunters.

262
00:23:44.742 --> 00:23:46.267
We will let them hunt us.

263
00:23:49.706 --> 00:23:50.939
Come.

264
00:24:04.679 --> 00:24:08.998
It is Tamacti Jun. We know you're here.

265
00:24:11.060 --> 00:24:12.752
Witchfinder General.

266
00:24:14.230 --> 00:24:16.548
Have you come to rejoin our ranks?

267
00:24:17.233 --> 00:24:21.010
Shiloh. I might have known.

268
00:24:22.989 --> 00:24:24.865
There will be no negotiating here.

269
00:24:24.949 --> 00:24:27.350
I had no intention of negotiating.

270
00:24:29.412 --> 00:24:30.812
They're on the roof.

271
00:24:34.042 --> 00:24:35.358
Get back!

272
00:24:44.928 --> 00:24:47.596
Maghra Kane. Where are you?

273
00:24:47.805 --> 00:24:49.122
I'm right here.

274
00:25:25.802 --> 00:25:28.370
Maghra!

275
00:25:35.311 --> 00:25:36.878
Where are the rest of you?

276
00:25:37.188 --> 00:25:39.398
What are you planning?

277
00:25:39.482 --> 00:25:45.053
You... You think I would betray
my oath to God for a heretic like you?

278
00:25:47.657 --> 00:25:49.766
You have no authority over them.

279
00:25:50.493 --> 00:25:53.103
They serve a different queen now.

280
00:25:53.913 --> 00:25:56.832
What queen? What are you talking about?

281
00:26:01.045 --> 00:26:02.671
You don't know?

282
00:26:07.135 --> 00:26:12.056
Sibeth and the Witchfinders
will rain God Thunder down

283
00:26:12.140 --> 00:26:14.874
on you and your devil children.

284
00:26:21.441 --> 00:26:26.112
You fight for a kingdom
that is already lost.

285
00:26:32.368 --> 00:26:36.539
You better kill me. Maghra Kane.
Or you will live to regret it.

286
00:26:36.623 --> 00:26:38.582
You're a Witchfinder
who can no longer walk.

287
00:26:38.666 --> 00:26:40.150
You're already dead.

288
00:26:41.127 --> 00:26:43.319
Kill me. you bitch!

289
00:26:50.553 --> 00:26:51.953
Shiloh.

290
00:26:52.722 --> 00:26:55.832
Tamacti Jun.

291
00:26:58.228 --> 00:27:02.881
Give me my honor. Finish me.

292
00:27:06.778 --> 00:27:09.220
Death must be earned. Shiloh.

293
00:27:11.032 --> 00:27:12.766
Trust me. I know.

294
00:27:15.370 --> 00:27:16.770
Kill me!

295
00:27:22.794 --> 00:27:24.545
Kill me!

296
00:27:31.052 --> 00:27:34.972
You're awake.

297
00:27:35.056 --> 00:27:36.289
Where are we?

298
00:27:37.976 --> 00:27:41.544
Well. based on the smell.
I'd say we're in their home.

299
00:27:43.982 --> 00:27:45.423
Smells like…

300
00:27:50.989 --> 00:27:52.239
Oh. no.

301
00:27:52.323 --> 00:27:53.866
What? What? What?

302
00:27:53.950 --> 00:27:57.811
They... They're eating people.

303
00:27:58.288 --> 00:27:59.813
Oh. my God.

304
00:28:00.874 --> 00:28:02.107
Guntar?

305
00:28:04.419 --> 00:28:05.586
Oh. shit.

306
00:28:07.714 --> 00:28:09.322
We have to get out of here.

307
00:28:10.383 --> 00:28:11.908
Yeah.

308
00:28:13.428 --> 00:28:15.495
I've been trying while you were asleep.

309
00:28:16.389 --> 00:28:18.724
They may be animals.
but they know their knots.

310
00:28:21.853 --> 00:28:24.295
Well. they'll come for us.

311
00:28:25.482 --> 00:28:29.718
Haniwa. if they could track us.
they'd be here already.

312
00:28:30.987 --> 00:28:34.389
And there's... there's Pennsa to consider.

313
00:28:35.241 --> 00:28:37.326
- What about it?
- Their first order of business remains.

314
00:28:37.410 --> 00:28:40.103
They gotta get home.
They gotta warn Maghra.

315
00:28:42.624 --> 00:28:44.649
My father won't leave me behind.

316
00:28:46.336 --> 00:28:48.445
Even for the sake of an entire kingdom?

317
00:28:49.297 --> 00:28:53.116
Yes. Even for that.

318
00:28:56.429 --> 00:28:57.871
Well…

319
00:28:59.390 --> 00:29:02.476
I guess there is some small comfort
in knowing

320
00:29:02.560 --> 00:29:05.754
that either way. we're dead.

321
00:29:17.200 --> 00:29:20.518
Hey. hey. hey.

322
00:29:22.163 --> 00:29:24.248
- Haniwa?
- Yeah?

323
00:29:24.332 --> 00:29:27.150
You know. we've never really talked.

324
00:29:29.003 --> 00:29:30.296
You're choosing now to start?

325
00:29:30.380 --> 00:29:32.840
Oh. I'm sorry.
do you have somewhere you need to be?

326
00:29:41.933 --> 00:29:46.127
Okay. Okay. um…

327
00:29:49.607 --> 00:29:53.736
Okay. Behind you. uh. there's some
broken glass about an arm's length.

328
00:29:53.820 --> 00:29:55.929
but you're going to have to move.

329
00:29:56.614 --> 00:29:58.032
- Yes.
- Which way. which way?

330
00:29:58.116 --> 00:30:00.242
Um. further back. Yes.

331
00:30:00.326 --> 00:30:03.662
About half an arm's length now.
Just a bit further.

332
00:30:05.957 --> 00:30:07.941
- Half an arm?
- Yes.

333
00:30:08.745 --> 00:30:10.567
You're very close. Almost there.

334
00:30:10.652 --> 00:30:12.786
- Further. further. further back.
- Okay.

335
00:30:12.871 --> 00:30:14.799
- I can't get further.
- Oh. shit.

336
00:30:14.883 --> 00:30:17.301
Yeah. Yeah. that's close.

337
00:30:17.385 --> 00:30:19.387
- Yeah. almost.
- Okay.

338
00:30:19.471 --> 00:30:21.722
Now he's coming. He's coming.

339
00:30:21.806 --> 00:30:24.558
- Where is it? Where is it?
- Oh. shh. Shh. Be quiet.

340
00:30:24.642 --> 00:30:26.778
- Don't...
- Then tell me quietly. Where is it?

341
00:30:26.863 --> 00:30:29.421
He's coming. He's coming.

342
00:30:30.690 --> 00:30:32.400
No. I've got it.

343
00:30:32.484 --> 00:30:34.443
Okay. Oh. fuck.

344
00:30:34.527 --> 00:30:37.571
- No! No!
- Oh. fuck. Oh. fuck.

345
00:30:46.414 --> 00:30:48.374
Lucien. is that you?

346
00:30:48.458 --> 00:30:49.774
Yes. my queen.

347
00:30:50.543 --> 00:30:52.152
We have the Trivantian scientist.

348
00:30:53.421 --> 00:30:54.654
Bring him.

349
00:31:04.849 --> 00:31:07.125
I hear chains. Why is he in chains?

350
00:31:07.811 --> 00:31:09.586
For your safety. Your Majesty.

351
00:31:10.563 --> 00:31:12.922
That is no way to treat
a new friend and ally.

352
00:31:13.525 --> 00:31:14.758
Unbind him.

353
00:31:15.568 --> 00:31:17.594
- My queen.
- Now.

354
00:31:22.075 --> 00:31:23.975
I am so sorry. Tormada.

355
00:31:24.536 --> 00:31:27.913
I suppose our nations have been at odds
for so long.

356
00:31:27.997 --> 00:31:29.647
you can hardly blame Lucien.

357
00:31:30.500 --> 00:31:33.359
If I were you and I'd captured me.
I'd have done the same.

358
00:31:34.420 --> 00:31:39.991
So. Trivantes and Paya are moments away
from a peace treaty.

359
00:31:41.094 --> 00:31:42.678
and you have planned an attack.

360
00:31:42.762 --> 00:31:47.082
Mmm. A treaty with your sister
wouldn't have given me much peace.

361
00:31:49.185 --> 00:31:52.087
And you're going to war
with only a handful of soldiers.

362
00:31:53.731 --> 00:31:55.316
I'm funny like that.

363
00:31:55.400 --> 00:31:58.324
Yes. I have heard about you.

364
00:31:59.863 --> 00:32:01.238
Your wonderful new weapons…

365
00:32:02.490 --> 00:32:05.975
…like thunder from the heavens
tearing apart the earth.

366
00:32:06.411 --> 00:32:08.287
An almost insurmountable advantage.

367
00:32:08.371 --> 00:32:12.690
Though. you don't speak
for all of Trivantes. do you?

368
00:32:13.960 --> 00:32:17.195
No more than you speak
for all of Paya. I suppose.

369
00:32:19.048 --> 00:32:21.801
Tormada. I think

370
00:32:21.885 --> 00:32:26.847
you and I may very well be friends.

371
00:32:26.931 --> 00:32:28.832
And how am I so fortunate?

372
00:32:30.226 --> 00:32:32.752
The enemy of my enemy is my friend.

373
00:32:33.730 --> 00:32:34.963
Or rival.

374
00:32:35.773 --> 00:32:39.509
I find myself wondering how this ends.

375
00:32:41.362 --> 00:32:44.639
If you're careful.
you just might keep your head.

376
00:32:44.908 --> 00:32:46.641
Oh. I'm certain I'll keep it.

377
00:32:47.368 --> 00:32:52.123
Because without it.
my bombs are just lumps of God bone

378
00:32:52.207 --> 00:32:54.441
and of no use to you at all.

379
00:32:54.918 --> 00:32:59.195
And without my bombs.
you'll never reclaim your kingdom.

380
00:33:00.548 --> 00:33:02.383
And without my army.

381
00:33:02.467 --> 00:33:08.079
you'll be vulnerable to attack
from Pennsa and Trivantes alike.

382
00:33:09.474 --> 00:33:14.502
Sounds like the perfect foundation
for a deal to be struck. Hmm?

383
00:33:17.106 --> 00:33:22.302
Tell me. my queen.
what is it that you want?

384
00:33:24.823 --> 00:33:26.723
I want my father's kingdom back.

385
00:33:27.325 --> 00:33:28.725
But why stop there?

386
00:33:29.577 --> 00:33:34.939
There's a whole world beyond Paya.
That's what I want.

387
00:33:36.167 --> 00:33:41.071
Once Paya is mine. you may use it
as your base to build new weapons.

388
00:33:41.756 --> 00:33:44.699
to expand your empire
as far as your heart desires.

389
00:33:45.301 --> 00:33:48.286
You don't strike me
as someone who likes to share.

390
00:33:49.139 --> 00:33:52.248
Well. not with just anyone.

391
00:33:53.184 --> 00:33:54.709
But a husband.

392
00:33:57.647 --> 00:33:59.005
A king.

393
00:34:00.358 --> 00:34:02.443
- Is that a proposal. Your Highness?
- My queen.

394
00:34:02.527 --> 00:34:04.653
- If so. I accept.
- Wait.

395
00:34:04.737 --> 00:34:07.740
Quiet. Lucien.
Can't you hear we're having a moment?

396
00:34:07.824 --> 00:34:11.017
You can't be serious about
aligning ourselves with a Trivantian.

397
00:34:11.494 --> 00:34:13.103
We cannot trust this man.

398
00:34:14.789 --> 00:34:16.106
Perhaps you're right.

399
00:34:18.668 --> 00:34:20.151
Hand me your sword.

400
00:34:21.671 --> 00:34:23.172
Your Majesty?

401
00:34:45.778 --> 00:34:49.764
What do you say. Tormada? Can I trust you?

402
00:34:50.909 --> 00:34:55.812
It's certainly a gamble.
I'll give you that.

403
00:34:57.373 --> 00:34:59.875
But you strike me
as someone who's spent years

404
00:34:59.959 --> 00:35:02.235
honing her instincts about people.

405
00:35:03.671 --> 00:35:04.904
Hmm?

406
00:35:05.590 --> 00:35:06.990
Indeed. I have.

407
00:35:34.494 --> 00:35:36.561
Thank you for your service.

408
00:35:53.428 --> 00:35:55.580
I ruled alone my entire life.

409
00:35:58.935 --> 00:36:00.335
It's exhausting.

410
00:36:02.981 --> 00:36:04.422
Lonely.

411
00:36:07.152 --> 00:36:10.011
I've just never met anyone
with the stomach for it.

412
00:36:12.657 --> 00:36:15.558
But you seem up to the task.

413
00:36:16.995 --> 00:36:22.315
I am. my queen. I am.

414
00:39:17.926 --> 00:39:19.367
Harlan.

415
00:39:21.638 --> 00:39:23.663
- Harlan.
- Shh.

416
00:39:32.232 --> 00:39:34.924
- This could be our only chance.
- Shh.

417
00:39:42.492 --> 00:39:43.892
You did it.

418
00:39:56.840 --> 00:39:58.239
Haniwa.

419
00:39:59.843 --> 00:40:02.285
I'm here.

420
00:40:03.847 --> 00:40:05.163
Harlan.

421
00:40:13.565 --> 00:40:14.857
Harlan!

422
00:42:59.689 --> 00:43:01.214
Haniwa.

423
00:43:02.066 --> 00:43:03.466
I'm here.

424
00:43:05.820 --> 00:43:07.446
Okay. okay.

425
00:43:09.991 --> 00:43:13.351
You came back.

426
00:43:13.995 --> 00:43:15.603
I never left.

427
00:43:16.498 --> 00:43:19.625
I just wanted to find something
really heavy to hit the fucker with.

428
00:43:27.383 --> 00:43:28.867
Oh.

429
00:43:31.221 --> 00:43:34.456
Okay. All right. we got to go.

430
00:43:36.851 --> 00:43:39.127
- Papa.
- Haniwa.

431
00:43:41.731 --> 00:43:43.566
- Are you hurt?
- No.

432
00:43:43.650 --> 00:43:45.675
- Haniwa.
- Where's Harlan?

433
00:43:46.069 --> 00:43:47.778
Almost sound worried about me. Boo-boo.

434
00:43:47.862 --> 00:43:49.488
- Harlan.
- Oh. no.

435
00:43:49.572 --> 00:43:52.265
- Ah. shit. Oh. God.
- Help.

436
00:43:52.826 --> 00:43:54.493
Wasn't as fast as I thought. was I?

437
00:43:56.704 --> 00:43:57.997
His cut is deep.

438
00:43:59.556 --> 00:44:03.666
It's okay. We can stop
the bleeding until we get him to a healer.

439
00:44:04.671 --> 00:44:06.696
Oh. Haniwa. g...

440
00:44:08.967 --> 00:44:11.618
Those weren't the last of their kind.
all right?

441
00:44:11.970 --> 00:44:13.554
There are more. and they'll be back.

442
00:44:13.638 --> 00:44:17.141
so all of you are gonna need
to move along pretty quickly.

443
00:44:17.225 --> 00:44:20.186
We are not leaving you here. Harlan.

444
00:44:20.270 --> 00:44:22.897
I don't think you're gonna have
much of a choice.

445
00:44:22.981 --> 00:44:24.672
No.

446
00:44:27.819 --> 00:44:31.054
It's okay. It's okay. it's okay.

447
00:44:32.157 --> 00:44:33.431
It's fine. really.

448
00:44:35.326 --> 00:44:40.146
Listen. I've been taking care of myself
for a long time. all right?

449
00:44:41.166 --> 00:44:43.358
It's nice to take care of someone else.

450
00:44:45.837 --> 00:44:47.876
- Thank you.
- No. thank you.

451
00:44:47.961 --> 00:44:50.779
See. this is nice. huh? Nice.

452
00:44:53.281 --> 00:44:55.907
All right. now listen to me.

453
00:44:57.526 --> 00:45:00.040
When you tell the story…

454
00:45:00.528 --> 00:45:02.430
…I want you to promise me

455
00:45:03.229 --> 00:45:06.618
you will massively exaggerate my bravery
in the face of certain death.

456
00:45:06.714 --> 00:45:08.489
Okay?

457
00:45:08.902 --> 00:45:11.153
Yes. Harlan. you were very brave.

458
00:45:11.532 --> 00:45:13.823
It's... It's good. It was very good.
Do it exactly like that.

459
00:45:17.428 --> 00:45:18.954
Wait. wait…

460
00:45:25.543 --> 00:45:27.944
Give this to Maghra. okay?

461
00:45:29.339 --> 00:45:32.007
And tell her that…

462
00:45:32.091 --> 00:45:35.577
…um... Yeah. tell her. uh…

463
00:45:36.054 --> 00:45:37.787
Uh. she…

464
00:45:45.104 --> 00:45:48.048
It's okay. She knows.

465
00:45:50.819 --> 00:45:52.528
Go. Come on. you gotta go.

466
00:45:52.612 --> 00:45:54.572
Hanging around
waiting for me to die is depressing.

467
00:45:54.656 --> 00:45:57.557
- Harlan.
- It's all right. Haniwa.

468
00:45:59.035 --> 00:46:00.870
Go on. Gotta go. Go.

469
00:46:00.977 --> 00:46:02.919
Oh. fuck.

470
00:46:05.041 --> 00:46:06.064
Oh. fuck.

471
00:46:07.900 --> 00:46:09.103
Oh. shit.

472
00:46:16.553 --> 00:46:17.869
Baba Voss.

473
00:46:20.640 --> 00:46:21.873
Yes. Harlan.

474
00:46:28.148 --> 00:46:30.256
Please don't let them take my city.

475
00:46:59.637 --> 00:47:00.870
Whoa.

476
00:47:37.300 --> 00:47:38.533
Hmm.

477
00:47:40.929 --> 00:47:42.954
I never had to fight for my crown.

478
00:47:44.641 --> 00:47:48.793
I was born into the monarchy.
a queen ordained by God.

479
00:47:50.522 --> 00:47:55.800
I wore the crown.
but it always felt a little light to me.

480
00:47:57.987 --> 00:48:04.392
But now. now that crown will be forged
in the burning flames of war.

481
00:48:05.537 --> 00:48:10.940
And I will be a queen reborn.
anointed by the blood of my enemies.

482
00:48:12.168 --> 00:48:14.611
You have the soul of a poet. my queen.

483
00:48:15.755 --> 00:48:17.072
Are we ready?

484
00:48:17.340 --> 00:48:18.573
We are.

485
00:48:18.883 --> 00:48:21.817
Good.
Let's begin.

486
00:48:22.305 --> 00:49:22.310
